<pdd-dependency>checkup_tools_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Goal
Write `pdd/checkup_planner.py`.

% Requirements
- Provide a deterministic planner for CI-safe and test-safe checkup runs.
- Provide an LLM planner for interactive runs. It MUST validate proposed tool
  names, append omitted available tools in deterministic order, and fall back
  to deterministic planning when the provider fails, returns no tools, or
  proposes an invalid plan.
- The LLM planner MUST accept an injected call adapter so its behavior is
  testable without network or provider access.
- Provide a factory that accepts documented planner names and rejects unknown names through the caller's CLI validation.
- Do not perform network or provider calls from deterministic planning.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Deterministic default
The deterministic planner MUST return a stable tool order for identical inputs.

R2 - Fail-safe interactive planning
An unavailable or invalid LLM planning result MUST degrade to the complete
deterministic plan rather than skip checks or fail the checkup session.
</contract_rules>

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/checkup_planner.py`
